00:20:27,585 --> 00:20:29,585
That was my best performance ever.

271
00:20:30,220 --> 00:20:31,114
I was amazing.

272
00:20:31,199 --> 00:20:32,919
You deserve the grand prize.

273
00:20:33,004 --> 00:20:34,803
I would like to thank my manager...

274
00:20:38,396 --> 00:20:40,325
I'm so relieved that you're on my side.

275
00:20:40,660 --> 00:20:43,014
Let's stay friends forever.

276
00:20:43,203 --> 00:20:44,345
Let's not be enemies.

277
00:20:44,430 --> 00:20:45,417
I know right.

278
00:20:46,040 --> 00:20:48,654
I'm truly glad that she's on my side.

279
00:20:51,496 --> 00:20:52,916
Hello.

280
00:20:53,941 --> 00:20:55,512
Hi, Kingkang.

281
00:21:02,631 --> 00:21:03,558
Hey...

282
00:21:04,186 --> 00:21:05,385
Kingkang, be quiet.

283
00:21:07,602 --> 00:21:09,688
He never barks at strangers.

284
00:21:09,773 --> 00:21:10,949
This is odd.

285
00:21:11,034 --> 00:21:12,006
Exactly.

286
00:21:14,011 --> 00:21:16,285
Well, that can happen.

287
00:21:16,513 --> 00:21:17,573
It's okay.

288
00:21:17,800 --> 00:21:19,253
Don't take it to heart.

289
00:21:19,469 --> 00:21:21,108
It's okay. It's okay.

290
00:21:22,073 --> 00:21:22,961
Calm down.

291
00:21:27,072 --> 00:21:28,706
Who could it be?
I'm not expecting anyone.

292
00:21:28,791 --> 00:21:29,644
Who is it?

293
00:21:32,046 --> 00:21:33,601
It's alright, Kingkang.

294
00:21:34,678 --> 00:21:36,145
No. It's fine.

295
00:21:42,731 --> 00:21:43,644
You?

296
00:21:43,829 --> 00:21:45,621
Now that you have a girlfriend and
new friends, you don't need me anymore?

297
00:21:46,921 --> 00:21:48,006
How did you get here?

298
00:21:48,268 --> 00:21:49,877
Why bother asking? Isn't it obvious?

299
00:21:49,962 --> 00:21:50,811
I followed you.

300
00:21:51,264 --> 00:21:52,226
Wow.

301
00:21:53,474 --> 00:21:54,871
I know you all.

302
00:21:55,810 --> 00:21:57,787
-Let me take a seat.
-You already did.

303
00:21:57,871 --> 00:21:59,871
This looks delicious.

304
00:22:00,269 --> 00:22:02,213
Since I haven't had dinner yet...

305
00:22:02,297 --> 00:22:03,139
Hold on.

306
00:22:03,224 --> 00:22:04,204
Please pay for it first.

307
00:22:04,289 --> 00:22:06,096
We all chipped in 10,000 won each.

308
00:22:06,706 --> 00:22:07,914
Tell him to pay for it.

309
00:22:09,833 --> 00:22:10,812
Jung Joohwan.

310
00:22:14,165 --> 00:22:15,796
You must have already told them, right?

311
00:22:16,104 --> 00:22:17,424
About your condition?

312
00:22:23,118 --> 00:22:25,118
Wow. So you did tell them.

313
00:22:25,544 --> 00:22:28,286
I was the only one who didn't know
that you told them.

314
00:22:28,371 --> 00:22:29,226
Actually...

315
00:22:29,948 --> 00:22:31,346
... something happened...

316
00:22:32,085 --> 00:22:36,449
It was very complicated.
That's why he couldn't tell you.

317
00:22:37,034 --> 00:22:39,675
I can't believe I have a foolish boss,

318
00:22:39,760 --> 00:22:42,383
who makes his girlfriend
talk in his stead.

319
00:22:45,906 --> 00:22:47,201
I'll raise your salary.

320
00:22:47,623 --> 00:22:49,857
I shall do my best to serve you.

321
00:22:53,550 --> 00:22:54,526
I envy you.

322
00:22:58,796 --> 00:22:59,995
Hey, there.

323
00:23:00,080 --> 00:23:01,607
What's your name?

324
00:23:03,303 --> 00:23:04,614
Geez, seriously...

325
00:23:05,449 --> 00:23:06,458
Why?

326
00:23:13,936 --> 00:23:15,293
Why? What's wrong?

327
00:23:20,862 --> 00:23:22,233
Hello, little doggie.

328
00:23:25,114 --> 00:23:27,114
Hello, little doggie.

329
00:23:31,280 --> 00:23:33,177
Gosh. Stop it already. Just go.

330
00:23:34,740 --> 00:23:36,484
Just sit back down.

331
00:23:38,264 --> 00:23:39,843
It's odd, isn't it?

332
00:23:40,008 --> 00:23:41,063
"Hello, little doggie."?

333
00:23:44,144 --> 00:23:45,724
You're such a good dog.

334
00:24:06,171 --> 00:24:08,093
Today was fun, wasn't it?

335
00:24:09,440 --> 00:24:11,440
Secretary Jung is such a nice person.

336
00:24:11,525 --> 00:24:14,800
That's why he's been working for me
for so long.

337
00:24:15,912 --> 00:24:17,912
They're all nice people.

338
00:24:18,930 --> 00:24:21,122
I'm talking about those
who have been staying by our sides.

339
00:24:21,521 --> 00:24:22,956
That's because you're a nice person.

340
00:24:24,271 --> 00:24:26,271
You're the one who's a nice person.

341
00:24:32,896 --> 00:24:34,315
This time around...

342
00:24:37,566 --> 00:24:38,770
... I was afraid.

343
00:24:45,068 --> 00:24:47,068
When I first had this illness...

344
00:24:47,500 --> 00:24:48,971
... the saddest thing to me...

345
00:24:49,694 --> 00:24:52,604
... was not being able to recognize
those whom I love.

346
00:24:54,040 --> 00:24:56,425
Because I couldn't recognize them...

347
00:24:57,767 --> 00:24:59,949
... I couldn't even love myself.

348
00:25:02,855 --> 00:25:05,194
But I thought wrong.

349
00:25:06,736 --> 00:25:08,457
Nothing has changed.

350
00:25:09,539 --> 00:25:10,938
I thought that if people change,

351
00:25:11,290 --> 00:25:13,160
things change too.

352
00:25:13,739 --> 00:25:15,642
I was only fooling myself.

353
00:25:16,867 --> 00:25:17,733
You are the one...

354
00:25:18,778 --> 00:25:20,852
... who thought me that.

355
00:25:29,428 --> 00:25:31,654
When my first symptoms appeared,

356
00:25:33,699 --> 00:25:36,002
I received help from someone.

357
00:25:38,709 --> 00:25:40,527
He's an absolute stranger...

358
00:25:40,757 --> 00:25:42,413
... but he risked his life for me.

359
00:25:44,839 --> 00:25:46,763
That's why I wanted to help others too.

360
00:25:50,094 --> 00:25:51,938
Every time I change into someone else...

361
00:25:52,849 --> 00:25:55,955
... I always prayed for time
to pass by quickly.

362
00:25:56,723 --> 00:25:58,825
But you have helped me...

363
00:26:01,143 --> 00:26:03,143
... to come out into the world.

364
00:26:06,029 --> 00:26:07,510
I got better.

365
00:26:09,093 --> 00:26:11,209
I've become a much better person.

366
00:26:25,235 --> 00:26:26,260
I'm going to...

367
00:26:27,349 --> 00:26:28,587
... reveal my illness.

368
00:26:31,014 --> 00:26:32,600
I've decided to trust...

369
00:26:34,457 --> 00:26:36,003
... the people I love.

370
00:26:45,532 --> 00:26:46,799
You've gone through a lot.

371
00:26:48,251 --> 00:26:49,548
All this time.

372
00:26:57,696 --> 00:26:58,739
I...

373
00:26:59,239 --> 00:27:00,381
... have an illness.

374
00:27:06,373 --> 00:27:08,500
When I had the car accident ten years ago,

375
00:27:09,109 --> 00:27:10,484
I injured my brain.

376
00:27:11,193 --> 00:27:12,099
So...

377
00:27:12,948 --> 00:27:14,948
... I can't recognize people's faces.

378
00:27:16,430 --> 00:27:17,499
What?

379
00:27:19,137 --> 00:27:20,537
What do you mean?

380
00:27:21,394 --> 00:27:22,661
Dad...

381
00:27:22,746 --> 00:27:26,251
What do you mean, you can't
recognize people's faces?

382
00:27:27,406 --> 00:27:28,697
That's exactly what it is.

383
00:27:29,722 --> 00:27:30,989
I have prosopagnosia.

384
00:27:31,625 --> 00:27:34,304
I can't remember your face, Grandpa.

385
00:27:34,735 --> 00:27:37,515
If you pretend to be someone else
and walk pass me...

386
00:27:38,130 --> 00:27:41,271
... I won't be able to recognize you.

387
00:27:44,257 --> 00:27:45,307
Is it serious?

388
00:27:45,392 --> 00:27:46,478
Yes.

389
00:27:49,207 --> 00:27:50,083
Can it be cured?

390
00:27:50,168 --> 00:27:51,171
No.

391
00:27:55,825 --> 00:27:56,665
You.

392
00:27:57,101 --> 00:27:58,316
Did you know about this?

393
00:28:01,300 --> 00:28:03,692
Yes, I do.

394
00:28:06,167 --> 00:28:07,215
What about you?

395
00:28:08,067 --> 00:28:09,557
Well...

396
00:28:10,298 --> 00:28:11,656
I didn't know.

397
00:28:13,347 --> 00:28:15,853
I know you're my daughter...

398
00:28:16,279 --> 00:28:18,892
... but how can you be so cruel?

399
00:28:18,977 --> 00:28:20,109
You knew it all along,

400
00:28:20,194 --> 00:28:24,649
yet you didn't say a thing
to your father nor your husband.

401
00:28:28,512 --> 00:28:30,512
Don't be mad at Mom.

402
00:28:31,465 --> 00:28:32,820
I was the one who wanted
to keep it a secret.

403
00:28:32,905 --> 00:28:36,270
You were about to kick
him out of the house...

404
00:28:36,839 --> 00:28:37,933
... if he had a single flaw.

405
00:28:39,346 --> 00:28:42,353
How do you expect Dojae to tell you that?

406
00:28:49,583 --> 00:28:50,819
Grandpa...

407
00:28:51,369 --> 00:28:52,331
... are you crying?

408
00:28:54,361 --> 00:28:56,262
How could I not?

409
00:28:56,404 --> 00:28:57,599
Why are you crying?

410
00:28:57,895 --> 00:29:01,232
Every word I ever said to you...

411
00:29:01,908 --> 00:29:03,627
... I regret them all.

412
00:29:04,273 --> 00:29:05,717
I'm sorry, that's why.

413
00:29:24,129 --> 00:29:26,129
It must have been hard for you.

414
00:29:27,228 --> 00:29:31,876
You must have really hated me
for not knowing anything.

415
00:29:32,515 --> 00:29:33,600
I'm sorry...

416
00:29:34,280 --> 00:29:35,534
... for not meeting your expectations.

417
00:29:35,619 --> 00:29:36,688
Nonsense.

418
00:29:37,450 --> 00:29:40,731
There's no grandson as good as you
in this country.

419
00:29:43,013 --> 00:29:45,463
Since we're all being honest,
I also have something to say.

420
00:29:50,690 --> 00:29:51,667
I...

421
00:29:53,056 --> 00:29:54,704
I'm not going to marry Kiho.

422
00:29:55,671 --> 00:29:56,658
Why not?

423
00:29:57,071 --> 00:29:59,323
What's wrong? Is he not treating you well?

424
00:29:59,796 --> 00:30:01,450
I don't love him.

425
00:30:02,429 --> 00:30:04,286
I only loved his social status.

426
00:30:07,867 --> 00:30:09,388
Don't get married.

427
00:30:10,228 --> 00:30:14,788
No one here has forced you
to marry that guy.

428
00:30:15,193 --> 00:30:16,818
I'm partly responsible.

429
00:30:18,619 --> 00:30:22,175
You needed his help in order to beat me.

430
00:30:22,516 --> 00:30:23,508
You're right.

431
00:30:23,625 --> 00:30:24,620
But...

432
00:30:25,285 --> 00:30:27,058
... it's not your fault.

433
00:30:27,761 --> 00:30:30,566
Even though I took your side just now...

434
00:30:32,595 --> 00:30:34,194
... that was all because of my greed.

435
00:30:34,906 --> 00:30:36,497
Everything...

436
00:30:36,936 --> 00:30:38,936
... is my fault.

437
00:30:39,123 --> 00:30:40,927
It's my fault.

438
00:30:41,018 --> 00:30:42,573
No, it's my fault.

439
00:30:42,902 --> 00:30:45,389
I made the kids fight each other.

440
00:30:45,505 --> 00:30:47,178
You can blame yourselves later.

441
00:30:47,338 --> 00:30:48,833
There's something more urgent.

442
00:30:49,280 --> 00:30:50,356
Mr. Choi...

443
00:30:51,013 --> 00:30:52,597
... knows about Dojae's condition.

444
00:30:53,173 --> 00:30:55,260
Director Kim might also
find out about it soon.

445
00:30:55,448 --> 00:30:56,484
After that...

446
00:30:57,371 --> 00:30:59,895
... he'll stop at nothing
to bring Dojae down.

447
00:31:01,772 --> 00:31:02,865
Choi Kiho.

448
00:31:03,423 --> 00:31:05,423
That fearless jerk.

449
00:31:05,645 --> 00:31:10,116
Director Kim, that fearless punk.

450
00:31:11,383 --> 00:31:13,383
Calm down.

451
00:31:13,816 --> 00:31:15,552
Don't get too worked up.

452
00:31:15,636 --> 00:31:17,253
Please calm down, you two.

453
00:31:17,345 --> 00:31:19,085
-Calm down.
-You beat me to it.

454
00:31:19,518 --> 00:31:21,518
I was going to tell on them first.

455
00:31:23,221 --> 00:31:24,751
If you feel guilty to me...

456
00:31:25,007 --> 00:31:26,921
... you should teach them a lesson.

457
00:31:27,006 --> 00:31:27,974
You...

458
00:31:29,099 --> 00:31:30,457
You...

459
00:31:32,390 --> 00:31:34,328
You fool.

460
00:31:35,579 --> 00:31:39,577
You can't handle that one thing,
and yet you want to take over my company?

461
00:31:40,119 --> 00:31:43,617
I can't give my company
to a fool like you.

462
00:31:43,702 --> 00:31:44,683
That's it.

463
00:31:45,056 --> 00:31:46,694
That's more like the grandpa I know.

464
00:31:48,584 --> 00:31:50,691
We're in such a good mood,
so I thought you're going to let it slide.

465
00:31:50,776 --> 00:31:53,127
Sunho Group is not going down,

466
00:31:53,212 --> 00:31:55,939
just because one
executive director is sick.

467
00:31:56,206 --> 00:31:57,263
Don't worry.

468
00:31:57,348 --> 00:31:59,473
I'll take on more work if it's necessary.

469
00:31:59,989 --> 00:32:01,184
Plus, we have Sara.

470
00:32:02,174 --> 00:32:03,616
That's what I'm worried about.

471
00:32:03,701 --> 00:32:05,431
If that's the case...

472
00:32:05,731 --> 00:32:07,401
... then, should I lend a hand
in the business too?

473
00:32:07,486 --> 00:32:09,870
Dad, you think running
a business is like a child's play?

474
00:32:10,353 --> 00:32:12,457
Just keep taking care of your flowers
like you always do.

475
00:32:26,464 --> 00:32:28,891
Kiho will definitely go berserk.

476
00:32:29,435 --> 00:32:30,288
I know.

477
00:32:30,407 --> 00:32:31,879
There's no way he'll sit back on this.

478
00:32:33,184 --> 00:32:34,399
You handle it.

479
00:32:40,202 --> 00:32:43,163
You should handle it
since you're my elder brother.

480
00:32:44,018 --> 00:32:45,290
I have somewhere to go.

481
00:32:53,151 --> 00:32:56,087
Yes. We just left the grocery store.

482
00:32:56,738 --> 00:32:57,591
Okay.

483
00:32:57,864 --> 00:32:58,933
Okay...

484
00:33:00,621 --> 00:33:04,066
Who was that? Why do you have
to report your whereabouts every time?

485
00:33:04,235 --> 00:33:05,335
None of your business.

486
00:33:07,070 --> 00:33:08,364
Do you have a girlfriend?

487
00:33:08,449 --> 00:33:10,063
-Get lost.
-You do.

488
00:33:10,148 --> 00:33:12,234
-I said get lost.
-You have a girlfriend.

489
00:33:12,768 --> 00:33:13,622
How old is she?

490
00:33:13,779 --> 00:33:14,630
Is she pretty?

491
00:33:14,838 --> 00:33:16,031
Is she on social media?

492
00:33:16,871 --> 00:33:18,525
Geez. Seriously.

493
00:33:22,265 --> 00:33:25,007
That is a super expensive car.

494
00:33:25,092 --> 00:33:25,943
Look.

495
00:33:36,007 --> 00:33:37,464
Why are you here?

496
00:33:41,824 --> 00:33:42,910
Who is this?

497
00:33:43,020 --> 00:33:44,474
I'm his sister.

498
00:33:44,822 --> 00:33:46,956
Ryu Eunho's younger sister.

499
00:33:49,112 --> 00:33:50,871
The one he doesn't get along with?

500
00:33:54,538 --> 00:33:57,476
You said you two don't get along.
I guess that was a lie.

501
00:34:00,106 --> 00:34:02,803
Let me steal your brother for a while.
Is that okay?

502
00:34:02,888 --> 00:34:04,916
Yes. Of course.

503
00:34:05,000 --> 00:34:06,194
Of course, you can.

504
00:34:06,279 --> 00:34:08,678
You can take him for as long as you want.

505
00:34:11,301 --> 00:34:12,880
Hurry. Go.

506
00:34:13,439 --> 00:34:15,994
Before this pretty lady changes her mind.

507
00:34:17,926 --> 00:34:18,923
Thank you.

508
00:34:20,974 --> 00:34:21,906
What's your name?

509
00:34:21,991 --> 00:34:24,292
I'm Ryu Aram.

510
00:34:24,377 --> 00:34:26,126
Thank you, Aram.

511
00:34:32,176 --> 00:34:34,192
You better not say anything
when you get home.

512
00:34:34,395 --> 00:34:35,536
Do you understand?

513
00:34:35,620 --> 00:34:37,035
Mind your own business.

514
00:34:38,304 --> 00:34:39,290
Go.

515
00:34:39,782 --> 00:34:40,801
Hurry.

516
00:34:44,105 --> 00:34:45,320
You can do it, Ryu Eunho!

517
00:34:45,637 --> 00:34:47,502
Best of luck!

518
00:34:54,112 --> 00:34:55,983
You better not lose her.

519
00:34:56,292 --> 00:34:57,869
If you do, I'll kill you.

520
00:35:01,566 --> 00:35:05,173
You paid for it last time.
So this time, it's my treat.

521
00:35:05,442 --> 00:35:06,492
I don't want that.

522
00:35:07,557 --> 00:35:08,766
Why not?

523
00:35:09,192 --> 00:35:10,571
I want to treat you.

524
00:35:11,033 --> 00:35:14,559
You said you never dated anyone.
How did you know all these things?

525
00:35:14,800 --> 00:35:16,395
Eunho?

526
00:35:22,384 --> 00:35:23,301
Dojae.

527
00:35:38,980 --> 00:35:40,770
Since when did you start
seeing each other?

528
00:35:41,378 --> 00:35:42,593
Since 6PM.

529
00:35:43,008 --> 00:35:45,364
You know that's what I'm asking.

530
00:35:46,062 --> 00:35:48,399
Dojae, you're in no position
to be mad at him.

531
00:35:50,325 --> 00:35:51,753
I'm the one who's chasing him.

532
00:35:51,838 --> 00:35:53,795
Hey! Why did you make her chase you?

533
00:35:53,880 --> 00:35:55,364
I didn't teach you
to treat women like that.

534
00:35:55,484 --> 00:35:56,669
What are you talking about?

535
00:35:57,432 --> 00:35:59,432
You wanted to be friends, but I said no.

536
00:36:02,561 --> 00:36:04,956
That's it. I taught him well.

537
00:36:05,306 --> 00:36:06,417
So...

538
00:36:07,304 --> 00:36:10,116
So, both of you are seriously...

539
00:36:10,812 --> 00:36:11,985
... in a relationship?

540
00:36:13,094 --> 00:36:15,094
-Since when?
-Since 6PM.

541
00:36:15,209 --> 00:36:16,558
Han Segye...

542
00:36:16,643 --> 00:36:18,417
... what do you like about Dojae?

543
00:36:19,275 --> 00:36:20,982
I just could not fathom.

544
00:36:23,015 --> 00:36:25,094
He knows me better than anyone else.

545
00:36:25,339 --> 00:36:26,618
He knows that I'm nice.

546
00:36:28,314 --> 00:36:29,853
