Manager Lee.

640
00:42:20,268 --> 00:42:22,162
I'm not crying.

641
00:42:23,404 --> 00:42:24,410
It's okay.

642
00:42:24,850 --> 00:42:26,610
Wait for me. Wait for me.

643
00:42:29,653 --> 00:42:30,871
Wait for me.

644
00:42:33,989 --> 00:42:35,525
You did a great job.

645
00:42:36,285 --> 00:42:37,799
I didn't do much.

646
00:42:38,082 --> 00:42:38,972
That's right.

647
00:42:39,303 --> 00:42:40,812
I did all the hard work.

648
00:42:42,653 --> 00:42:43,523
Well...

649
00:42:43,815 --> 00:42:44,958
That, I agree.

650
00:42:45,372 --> 00:42:46,363
You did well.

651
00:42:47,784 --> 00:42:49,833
Can you not use the past tense?

652
00:42:49,918 --> 00:42:51,544
I'll still have a lot of work to do.

653
00:42:51,628 --> 00:42:52,616
What can you do?

654
00:42:52,970 --> 00:42:55,306
Your boss keeps giving you more work.

655
00:42:55,644 --> 00:42:56,700
It's fine.

656
00:42:57,148 --> 00:42:59,027
It's an investment for my future.

657
00:42:59,446 --> 00:43:01,912
You need to be the CEO
so that I can become a president.

658
00:43:04,390 --> 00:43:06,729
I'll make sure that it'll go smoothly.

659
00:43:07,307 --> 00:43:08,464
I'm a genius, you know.

660
00:43:08,592 --> 00:43:09,505
I'm competent.

661
00:43:09,589 --> 00:43:11,000
Have you still not given up on that dream?

662
00:43:11,085 --> 00:43:12,184
It's not a dream.

663
00:43:12,269 --> 00:43:14,256
It's a realistic goal.

664
00:43:15,030 --> 00:43:16,209
I think...

665
00:43:16,331 --> 00:43:18,713
... word will slowly start leaking by now.

666
00:43:19,013 --> 00:43:20,040
What's your next plan?

667
00:43:20,125 --> 00:43:21,461
Next...

668
00:43:23,926 --> 00:43:25,102
... we wait.

669
00:43:28,382 --> 00:43:29,231
What?

670
00:43:29,828 --> 00:43:31,720
Face blindness?

671
00:43:31,805 --> 00:43:34,692
Yes. He told his staff about it today.

672
00:43:34,776 --> 00:43:35,885
Personally.

673
00:43:37,935 --> 00:43:39,819
Is it a serious illness?

674
00:43:40,853 --> 00:43:43,748
I'm bad at recognizing people too, though.

675
00:43:44,029 --> 00:43:45,036
So?

676
00:43:45,329 --> 00:43:47,257
What is it exactly like?

677
00:43:47,498 --> 00:43:49,481
Does he have bad eyesight or something?

678
00:43:49,566 --> 00:43:50,772
Explain so that I can understand.

679
00:43:50,856 --> 00:43:54,585
All I know is that he can't tell
who's who by just looking at their faces.

680
00:43:54,670 --> 00:43:55,648
What?

681
00:43:57,894 --> 00:44:00,577
Then again, the symptoms
are not important.

682
00:44:00,735 --> 00:44:03,167
What matters is that he has an illness.

683
00:44:03,252 --> 00:44:05,811
How can we entrust the company
to a sick person?

684
00:44:05,896 --> 00:44:08,652
We can't. It's a bad idea.

685
00:44:10,447 --> 00:44:13,516
This must be what Choi Kiho
has been keeping from me.

686
00:44:14,249 --> 00:44:15,274
(Choi Kiho, Dashi Tour)

687
00:44:20,647 --> 00:44:21,750
(Director Kim, T'road Airline)

688
00:44:26,156 --> 00:44:28,395
Hello, Mr. Choi. Have you heard the news?

689
00:44:28,480 --> 00:44:30,480
-What news?
-You know...

690
00:44:30,769 --> 00:44:34,354
Apparently, Mr. Seo has a sad story.

691
00:44:35,673 --> 00:44:37,673
I feel so sorry for him.

692
00:44:38,210 --> 00:44:39,467
He...  What is it called, again?

693
00:44:39,552 --> 00:44:40,716
Prosopagnosia.

694
00:44:40,868 --> 00:44:43,532
Prosopagnosia? That one.

695
00:44:43,821 --> 00:44:46,077
He already revealed...

696
00:44:46,162 --> 00:44:48,273
... the card you've been holding.

697
00:44:48,939 --> 00:44:52,321
Mr. Seo is truly impressive.

698
00:44:52,406 --> 00:44:54,143
Did he reveal it himself?

699
00:44:54,227 --> 00:44:56,014
Yes, he did.

700
00:44:56,678 --> 00:44:57,828
Oh no.

701
00:44:57,913 --> 00:44:59,913
You must be very disappointed.

702
00:45:01,760 --> 00:45:03,209
See?

703
00:45:03,294 --> 00:45:05,680
You should've told me
from the very beginning.

704
00:45:05,863 --> 00:45:08,253
Business is all about collaboration.

705
00:45:13,085 --> 00:45:14,051
Turn the car around.

706
00:45:15,198 --> 00:45:16,538
Turn the car around!

707
00:45:19,929 --> 00:45:22,267
-You're not allowed to enter...
-Let me go.

708
00:45:30,246 --> 00:45:32,246
It's okay. You may leave.

709
00:45:33,488 --> 00:45:34,496
Yes, ma'am.

710
00:45:38,412 --> 00:45:40,359
Isn't it basic manner to knock first?

711
00:45:40,443 --> 00:45:41,897
Why did you reveal it this way?

712
00:45:42,797 --> 00:45:43,967
Are you insane?

713
00:45:47,508 --> 00:45:49,091
You said it was a gift.

714
00:45:51,154 --> 00:45:53,394
It's my right to use it however I want.

715
00:45:55,654 --> 00:45:57,079
Or was it a bomb?

716
00:45:57,902 --> 00:46:00,516
Then, I threw it at you.

717
00:46:00,601 --> 00:46:01,513
Kang Sara.

718
00:46:01,598 --> 00:46:02,503
I...

719
00:46:04,087 --> 00:46:05,566
I'm not marrying you.

720
00:46:08,152 --> 00:46:09,914
You've really lost your mind.

721
00:46:10,246 --> 00:46:12,835
I helped you out of pity.
But this is how you repay me?

722
00:46:12,982 --> 00:46:14,649
You really don't know what's scary, right?

723
00:46:14,734 --> 00:46:15,918
I do know.

724
00:46:17,336 --> 00:46:19,589
I almost joined your side.

725
00:46:22,231 --> 00:46:24,030
That's what's really scary.

726
00:46:24,237 --> 00:46:26,237
Don't push my limits.

727
00:46:26,712 --> 00:46:29,031
I went easy on you
because you're a woman.

728
00:46:30,686 --> 00:46:31,682
Who are you?

729
00:46:31,766 --> 00:46:32,653
A delivery man.

730
00:46:34,629 --> 00:46:35,829
What's his deal?

731
00:46:35,950 --> 00:46:37,063
What's going on between you two?

732
00:46:37,148 --> 00:46:38,373
I called him here.

733
00:46:38,573 --> 00:46:39,905
I have something to send.

734
00:46:41,214 --> 00:46:43,711
I had my doubts, but I guess I was right.

735
00:46:43,796 --> 00:46:46,727
You caused all this mess
because of some guy?

736
00:46:46,812 --> 00:46:48,635
Kang Sara, are you serious?

737
00:46:48,720 --> 00:46:51,348
Do you really think
it's just because of one guy?

738
00:46:51,432 --> 00:46:53,733
There are many guys involved in this.

739
00:47:06,638 --> 00:47:07,907
Are you okay?

740
00:47:09,722 --> 00:47:10,989
I'm not okay.

741
00:47:15,574 --> 00:47:18,420
I wanted to show you
what I was throwing away.

742
00:47:19,926 --> 00:47:21,316
That's why I called you here.

743
00:47:23,054 --> 00:47:24,137
I also...

744
00:47:27,979 --> 00:47:29,452
I also want to throw away everything.

745
00:47:30,821 --> 00:47:31,966
Then, do it.

746
00:47:44,440 --> 00:47:45,972
Mr. Choi from Dashi Tour.

747
00:47:46,191 --> 00:47:47,089
What brings you here?

748
00:47:47,173 --> 00:47:48,815
I can see why you two are siblings.

749
00:47:48,900 --> 00:47:50,655
You're both insane.

750
00:47:52,297 --> 00:47:53,607
You're still as rude as ever.

751
00:47:53,692 --> 00:47:54,663
You've heard, right?

752
00:47:54,927 --> 00:47:56,824
Your sister is not marrying me.

753
00:47:58,032 --> 00:47:59,595
So, I'm terminating our contract.

754
00:47:59,680 --> 00:48:00,517
Go ahead.

755
00:48:04,355 --> 00:48:07,310
I don't think you
understand the situation.

756
00:48:08,294 --> 00:48:09,429
You're sick.

757
00:48:10,662 --> 00:48:12,744
Do you know how bad that is for business?

758
00:48:12,872 --> 00:48:14,428
How would I know?

759
00:48:17,077 --> 00:48:18,847
(Strategic Planning)

760
00:48:18,932 --> 00:48:20,106
(Agreement with Dashi Tour)

761
00:48:22,659 --> 00:48:23,660
